389
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,777
♪ Happy birthday to you. ♪

390
00:31:15,355 --> 00:31:16,555
♪ Happy birthday to you. ♪

391
00:31:17,488 --> 00:31:21,088
♪ Happy birthday, happy birthday. ♪

392
00:31:22,555 --> 00:31:28,066
Happy birthday to you.

393
00:32:31,044 --> 00:32:34,733
I almost forgot.
I have another present for you.

394
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:38,977
The surprise continues.

395
00:32:39,977 --> 00:32:41,444
We have to give it to her though.

396
00:32:41,688 --> 00:32:44,466
She went overboard
with the party tonight.

397
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,044
I mean, I've been living here for years.

398
00:32:46,044 --> 00:32:48,533
And yet I didn't know there was
a company that does birthday parties.

399
00:32:49,311 --> 00:32:54,822
You're in awe, aren't you?
Did you forget I'm a director?

400
00:32:55,844 --> 00:32:58,533
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

401
00:33:00,333 --> 00:33:02,488
Open it. See if you like it.

402
00:33:11,133 --> 00:33:13,400
Gosh. It's pretty.

403
00:33:14,444 --> 00:33:17,111
Let me. I'll put it on you.

404
00:33:21,244 --> 00:33:23,600
May you know nothing but happiness.

405
00:33:25,066 --> 00:33:26,977
I'll give you my present later.

406
00:33:27,511 --> 00:33:28,488
Keep your promise.

407
00:33:29,133 --> 00:33:30,244
Or I'll keep pestering you for it.

408
00:33:32,733 --> 00:33:37,755
Let's do something fun tonight.

409
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:38,844
Don't fall into her trap.

410
00:33:38,844 --> 00:33:42,444
Her fun usually means
different from our fun.

411
00:33:42,555 --> 00:33:43,755
What do you suggest, then?

412
00:33:44,533 --> 00:33:46,422
- Play a game.
- Here we go.

413
00:33:46,511 --> 00:33:47,488
What game?

414
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,577
It's a psychological game.

415
00:33:49,688 --> 00:33:52,622
Let your guard down
and she'll hypnotize you.

416
00:33:52,955 --> 00:33:55,688
Wang, you make it
sound like I'm a witch.

417
00:33:55,822 --> 00:33:59,044
I do this all the time
with my actors. They're fine.

418
00:33:59,844 --> 00:34:04,644
The game is called 'tell the truth'.

419
00:34:05,355 --> 00:34:09,511
The game preys on those
who want to talk about themselves

420
00:34:09,711 --> 00:34:13,466
and at the same time
can't resist being nosy.

421
00:34:13,866 --> 00:34:15,444
See? I told you.

422
00:34:15,733 --> 00:34:18,044
It's fun, though.

423
00:34:18,266 --> 00:34:20,066
Let's start with something easy.

424
00:34:20,555 --> 00:34:23,933
The keyword is my idol.

425
00:34:24,911 --> 00:34:27,311
I have to talk about my idol?

426
00:34:27,644 --> 00:34:28,333
You're right.

427
00:34:28,533 --> 00:34:29,711
I'll go first.

428
00:34:30,377 --> 00:34:34,200
My idol is

429
00:34:34,488 --> 00:34:36,866
Elizabeth Taylor.

430
00:34:36,911 --> 00:34:39,088
- Who is that?
- Oh my god, Wang.

431
00:34:39,288 --> 00:34:41,688
How could you not know her
when your mom is a director?

432
00:34:42,244 --> 00:34:46,511
Elizabeth Taylor was a great actress.

433
00:34:46,733 --> 00:34:48,288
She was very pretty.

434
00:34:48,288 --> 00:34:51,822
She was one of the biggest stars in Hollywood.

435
00:34:51,844 --> 00:34:53,288
Does that mean she's still active?

436
00:34:53,755 --> 00:34:54,622
She died.

437
00:34:55,911 --> 00:34:57,244
What do you like about her?

438
00:34:59,711 --> 00:35:01,488
I don't know if I can say this
without getting embarrassed.

439
00:35:01,866 --> 00:35:05,244
But the game is for us to tell the truth.

440
00:35:05,555 --> 00:35:09,844
She's my idol because she was pretty.

441
00:35:09,930 --> 00:35:12,755
She was kind and she was smart.

442
00:35:12,933 --> 00:35:16,733
And the most important thing
is she got married eight times.

443
00:35:17,911 --> 00:35:20,044
Eight times? That means
she had eight husbands?

444
00:35:20,755 --> 00:35:24,755
Seven. She re-married
one of her ex-husbands.

445
00:35:26,311 --> 00:35:28,711
Now, it's your turn.

446
00:35:30,822 --> 00:35:32,244
My idol is.

447
00:35:35,244 --> 00:35:37,333
I guess it's my social studies
teacher at the boarding school.

448
00:35:40,488 --> 00:35:42,066
This is disappointing.

449
00:35:42,333 --> 00:35:43,777
I thought you were going to say me.

450
00:35:45,266 --> 00:35:47,311
Do explain. How is he your idol?

451
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:54,444
He didn't only teach what's in textbooks.

452
00:35:55,933 --> 00:35:58,444
He taught us how to look for what's not in them, too.

453
00:35:59,311 --> 00:36:01,422
When the whole school got together and
called out the principal for corruption,

454
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,888
all the other teachers
didn't say a word.

455
00:36:04,533 --> 00:36:07,800
Only this social studies teacher
had something to say.

456
00:36:08,977 --> 00:36:10,177
And in the end what happened?

457
00:36:10,533 --> 00:36:14,088
You lost because you didn't have proof.

458
00:36:14,377 --> 00:36:16,044
You're right. We lost.

459
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:20,244
But it made us more aware of
injustice we have to fight to get rid of.

460
00:36:20,666 --> 00:36:23,755
We get it. You're a fighter.

461
00:36:24,733 --> 00:36:26,800
It's your turn, In.

462
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,088
Now?

463
00:36:30,377 --> 00:36:31,711
The 52-hertz whale.

464
00:36:31,977 --> 00:36:34,022
What? Did I hear that right?

465
00:36:34,511 --> 00:36:35,844
You cheated.

466
00:36:36,133 --> 00:36:39,355
You didn't say it had to be a person.

467
00:36:39,644 --> 00:36:40,533
You're sly.

468
00:36:40,777 --> 00:36:43,133
I know you did this on purpose.

469
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:46,955
I didn't. The 52-hertz whale
really is my idol.

470
00:36:47,177 --> 00:36:48,288
You avoided the question.

471
00:36:48,444 --> 00:36:51,333
Your technique isn't working on him.

472
00:36:52,377 --> 00:36:54,422
I know who your idol is.

473
00:36:54,555 --> 00:36:56,200
You're just afraid to bring him up.

474
00:36:56,288 --> 00:36:57,133
Who is it?

475
00:36:57,711 --> 00:37:00,444
It's because I know you're trying to set me up.

476
00:37:09,155 --> 00:37:12,150
(180 Degree Longitude Passes Through Us)

477
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,644
The 52-hertz whale. I like this answer.

478
00:37:15,644 --> 00:37:16,644
So, you know him?

479
00:37:17,155 --> 00:37:20,133
He calls at the frequency of 52 hertz.

480
00:37:20,311 --> 00:37:23,044
