00:37:30,044 --> 00:37:32,688
It's because I know you're trying to set me up.

483
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,577
The phone saved you.

484
00:37:47,022 --> 00:37:47,711
Hello?

485
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:52,222
For you, Mol.

486
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,444
It must be Elsa.

487
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:58,377
I called her this afternoon
and left her your number.

488
00:38:08,266 --> 00:38:10,533
Hello. What are you calling for?

489
00:38:11,711 --> 00:38:15,133
The 52-hertz whale. I like this answer.

490
00:38:16,622 --> 00:38:18,066
So, you know him?

491
00:38:20,688 --> 00:38:23,711
He calls at the frequency of 52 hertz.

492
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:29,866
No one hears him.
He's alone in the ocean.

493
00:38:30,977 --> 00:38:32,622
No one knows where he is.

494
00:38:34,822 --> 00:38:35,511
He's lonely.

495
00:38:37,711 --> 00:38:38,911
How do you know he's lonely?

496
00:38:41,644 --> 00:38:43,288
I'll look for the perfect dress.

497
00:38:43,844 --> 00:38:45,622
Can you book me a flight?

498
00:38:46,310 --> 00:38:51,000
Good news. I was nominated.

499
00:38:51,155 --> 00:38:56,400
Outstanding Director of the year
for Kom Chuen Kom Award.

500
00:38:57,622 --> 00:39:00,222
The award is taking place
the day after tomorrow.

501
00:39:00,222 --> 00:39:02,711
Congrats. I'm happy for you.

502
00:39:03,222 --> 00:39:09,866
Elsa told me I could win this
and even Best Lakorn.

503
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,955
He told me it's because
my lakorn is different.

504
00:39:12,133 --> 00:39:15,355
The other four contenders are all BL.

505
00:39:15,466 --> 00:39:17,266
All couples are gay.

506
00:39:17,533 --> 00:39:19,022
What project landed you the nomination?

507
00:39:19,666 --> 00:39:21,088
Silver Sand Castle.

508
00:39:22,288 --> 00:39:24,222
They say my presence is mandatory.

509
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,266
The award will be after tomorrow.

510
00:39:26,422 --> 00:39:28,577
I'll have to fly back tomorrow.

511
00:39:28,688 --> 00:39:30,666
After that, I'll have to look for
the perfect dress.

512
00:39:30,888 --> 00:39:33,377
I'll fly here after the award.

513
00:39:35,488 --> 00:39:37,711
Honey, do you want
to accompany me to the award show?

514
00:39:38,733 --> 00:39:40,000
I'd rather stay here.

515
00:39:40,466 --> 00:39:41,600
I don't want to trouble you
with a plane ticket.

516
00:39:43,555 --> 00:39:45,466
Now you're worried
about what's in my purse?

517
00:39:46,622 --> 00:39:53,111
Wang, he's never shown interest
in the entertainment industry.

518
00:39:53,311 --> 00:39:55,755
Otherwise, he would've become an actor.

519
00:39:55,755 --> 00:39:58,155
Right? You could be
making money for us.

520
00:39:59,666 --> 00:40:01,488
Take care of him for two days.

521
00:40:01,711 --> 00:40:03,600
I'm sure you could handle him?

522
00:40:05,488 --> 00:40:07,044
I'll leave the car with you.

523
00:40:07,288 --> 00:40:09,466
In case, you want to go
explore the nightlife in the city.

524
00:40:09,460 --> 00:40:11,022
You can't ask In to be your driver.

525
00:40:11,555 --> 00:40:15,933
I'm gonna go pack my things. I don't
want it to be chaotic tomorrow morning.

526
00:40:18,911 --> 00:40:20,622
What about the game?

527
00:40:21,133 --> 00:40:22,644
Do it with In.

528
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,266
But you were the one who wanted us to play.

529
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:44,822
Happy birthday.

530
00:40:48,777 --> 00:40:49,666
Thank you.

531
00:40:52,088 --> 00:40:53,022
I told you.

532
00:40:54,822 --> 00:40:56,288
Today wasn't special.

533
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:46,177
Do you know why she bought me the necklace?

534
00:41:48,466 --> 00:41:49,244
Why?

535
00:41:50,755 --> 00:41:51,688
Because she is jealous of Dad.

536
00:41:54,133 --> 00:41:58,866
She wanted me to take her with me
everywhere I go. Like I do with Dad.

537
00:42:00,733 --> 00:42:02,911
You're being unfair to her.

538
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:05,333
She loves you. You know that.

539
00:42:14,577 --> 00:42:16,888
Why is the 52-hertz whale your idol?

540
00:42:21,244 --> 00:42:22,933
Because he can live on his own.

541
00:42:24,222 --> 00:42:26,555
No one hears
what he says but that's fine.

542
00:42:28,266 --> 00:42:29,933
It doesn't matter
no one understands him.

543
00:42:31,288 --> 00:42:32,622
And no one can find him.

544
00:42:35,244 --> 00:42:36,111
And he isn't lonely?

545
00:42:38,488 --> 00:42:40,155
No one knows if he's lonely.

546
00:42:41,777 --> 00:42:43,222
That's his nature.

547
00:42:45,888 --> 00:42:46,688
I think he's lonely.

548
00:42:48,133 --> 00:42:50,311
You can't think for others, remember?

549
00:42:51,644 --> 00:42:54,844
You think he's lonely. Because you're lonely.

550
00:42:59,777 --> 00:43:00,600
I guess you're right.

551
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:03,933
I'm lonely.

552
00:43:06,770 --> 00:43:07,511
It's not wrong to be lonely.

553
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:09,844
We're human, after all.

554
00:43:11,022 --> 00:43:12,466
We weren't wired like the 52-hertz whale.

555
00:43:13,777 --> 00:43:14,466
In.

556
00:43:15,155 --> 00:43:15,622
What?

557
00:43:16,666 --> 00:43:18,155
Why didn't you just answer it?

558
00:43:20,022 --> 00:43:21,400
Who is it Mom mentioned earlier?

559
00:43:22,488 --> 00:43:23,600
Who is your idol?

560
00:43:28,310 --> 00:43:34,044
You think you're sending out a certain
frequency no one hears like that whale.

561
00:43:36,244 --> 00:43:37,155
But I hear you.

562
00:43:42,177 --> 00:43:43,244
Your idol is my dad, right?

563
00:43:52,377 --> 00:43:54,511
Can I ask my birthday
present from you now?

564
00:43:57,177 --> 00:44:00,377
If it's something I can give you.

565
00:44:03,333 --> 00:44:04,822
Can you tell me if Dad…

566
00:44:07,177 --> 00:44:13,466
- If Dad...
- The two of us were sorry it happened.

567
00:44:20,466 --> 00:44:22,600
We were really sorry it happened.

568
00:45:03,533 --> 00:45:04,911
You're not done packing?

569
00:45:05,133 --> 00:45:06,488
You'll be only there for a few days.

570
00:45:06,711 --> 00:45:08,288
I'm a lady. Did you forget?

571
00:45:08,420 --> 00:45:11,955
Drive safe. I hope you win tomorrow.

572
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:15,311
Your mom isn't here. Do you want to explore the city?

573
00:45:15,555 --> 00:45:16,577
I want to stay here.

574
00:45:17,666 --> 00:45:18,844
Jump over here.

575
00:45:19,111 --> 00:45:20,511
I bet you're afraid.

576
00:45:22,044 --> 00:45:25,288
Do you know you're talented?

577
00:45:27,044 --> 00:45:31,933
It doesn't matter if I'm talented
when I do nothing about it.
